# Development Workflow and Testing

## Development Scripts
- `npm run dev` - Start development server with Turbopack
- `npm run build` - Build production version
- `npm start` - Start production server
- `npm run lint` - Run ESLint
- `npm run test` - Run Vitest tests
- `npm run test-e2e` - Run Playwright end-to-end tests
- `npm run test:ci` - Run CI tests (lint + unit tests)

## Code Quality Tools
- **ESLint**: [eslintrc.js](mdc:eslintrc.js) and [.eslintrc](mdc:.eslintrc) - Linting configuration
- **Biome**: [biome.jsonc](mdc:biome.jsonc) - Fast linter and formatter
- **TypeScript**: [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json) - Type checking configuration

## Testing Setup
- **Unit Tests**: Vitest configuration in [vitest.config.ts](mdc:vitest.config.ts)
- **Test Setup**: [vitest.setup.ts](mdc:vitest.setup.ts) - Test environment setup
- **Jest Config**: [jest.config.ts](mdc:jest.config.ts) - Alternative Jest setup
- **Jest Setup**: [jest.setup.js](mdc:jest.setup.js) - Jest environment
- **E2E Tests**: [playwright.config.ts](mdc:playwright.config.ts) - Playwright configuration
- **Test Files**: `__tests__/` directories throughout the project

## Asset Management
- **Static Assets**: [public/](mdc:public) - Public static files
- **Styles**: [styles/](mdc:styles) - Sass/CSS files
- **Images**: Optimized with Next.js Image component

## Development Environment
- **Node.js**: Uses latest LTS version
- **Package Manager**: npm (with bun.lockb indicating Bun compatibility)
- **Hot Reload**: Turbopack for fast development builds
- **Environment Variables**: Uses dotenv for local development

## Build and Deployment
- **Vercel**: Optimized for Vercel deployment
- **Post-install**: Automatic Prisma client generation
- **Production**: Optimized builds with Next.js
